      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/domains/computing/domains/internet/domains/fediverse/texts/cultural-guide-for-fediverse-newcomers/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Hey y&amp;rsquo;all, my name is &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../personal/terms/emsenn.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;emsenn&lt;/a&gt;, and I&amp;rsquo;ve had an account in the &lt;a href=&#34;../terms/fediverse.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Fediverse&lt;/a&gt; for about decade. I&amp;rsquo;ve been interested in online networking for most of my life, though, so even though I haven&amp;rsquo;t been in this network for that long, I have some thoughts I would like to share, especially for people who are just now going the Fediverse, or looking to become a bit more a part of its culture.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
